SENATE BILL 2564
By Bowling
HOUSE BILL 2304
By Barrett
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 2,
relative to elections.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 2, Chapter 3, Part 3, is amended by
deleting the part.
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 2, Chapter 6, Part 1, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
(a) Early voting satellite locations established by a county election commission
must:
(1) Be placed in geographic locations to include not more than four (4)
precincts;
(2) Be evenly distributed throughout the county to ensure that the
precincts are readily accessible;
(3) Utilize a secure, serialized, watermarked, hand-marked paper ballot;
(4) Maintain a separate check-in process for voters to obtain a ballot by
precinct; and
(5) Ensure that all ballots are secured and placed in an optical scanner
by individual precinct only and that ballots are segregated by precinct and are not
co-mingled with ballots from other precincts.
(b) The coordinator of elections shall promulgate rules to implement subsection
(a), including:
(1) A requirement for the use of precinct-based optical scanners or the
use of secure ballot boxes for each precinct;
HB2304
