- 1 -

(2) A requirement to utilize secure, serialized, watermarked, hand-
marked paper ballots and the provision for the correct ballot type representing
the satellite precinct(s); and
(3) The procedures for the process at the end of early voting to return the
optical scanners or secure ballot boxes, or both, which are to remain in the
county election commission office until such time as tabulation commences on
election day.
(c)
(1) Voting at a satellite location must cease at the end of the early voting
period.
(2) On election day, a voter shall only vote in the precinct where the voter
resides.
SECTION 3. This act takes effect upon becoming a law, the public welfare requiring it.
